1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:37,900
=Episode 9=

19
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:40,710
Stop running. Stop fooling around.

20
00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:42,480
Your uncle played drums,

21
00:01:42,973 --> 00:01:44,030
played a Japanese soldier,

22
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:45,000
and kneaded dough.

23
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:46,750
What does your uncle even do?

24
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:47,910
Cut it out.

25
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:48,750
I'm asking you.

26
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:49,800
Laidi.

27
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:50,640
Zhang Heiwa.

28
00:01:50,670 --> 00:01:51,510
What are you doing?

29
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:52,760
Come catch the water. Hurry.

30
00:01:52,771 --> 00:01:54,110
- Hurry.
- My clothes are soaked.

31
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,000
Careful. Hurry.

32
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,160
Can I...

33
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:57,350
Stop playing around.

34
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,640
Use your hands.

35
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Just knead the dough.

36
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,230
Why are you whining like that?

37
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:08,560
You're giving me the chills.

38
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:09,880
Stop talking to me.

39
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:11,750
So annoying.

40
00:02:11,750 --> 00:02:12,600
What's your problem?

41
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:21,990
Hu Sanyuan.

42
00:02:23,070 --> 00:02:23,960
I'm talking to you.

43
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,480
What is it?

44
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,510
Zhang Guangrong wrote.

45
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:45,480
What happened?

46
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,840
He agreed to the divorce.

47
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,200
Put it down. You'll burn your hand.

48
00:03:27,303 --> 00:03:28,680
What are you staring at? Four each.

49
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,000
No more. Go, go.

50
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,310
Hurry up, go.

51
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,600
Exactly.

52
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:38,120
I've got good news for you all.

53
00:03:39,790 --> 00:03:40,630
Come on.

54
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:42,760
Guess.

55
00:03:42,790 --> 00:03:44,000
What am I holding?

56
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,680
A lunchbox.

57
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,840
Obviously.

58
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:49,310
What's in the lunch box?

59
00:03:49,310 --> 00:03:50,150
Steamed stuffed buns.

60
00:03:50,610 --> 00:03:51,470
Red-braised pork.

61
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:53,240
You could guess till dawn and miss it.

62
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,280
Come on.

63
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,870
This is the first money

64
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:01,430
you've ever earned.

65
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,000
Two yuan each.

66
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:07,280
(Two yuan was the largest sum)

67
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,190
(Yi Qing'e had ever seen.)

68
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:12,840
(It could buy 40 white-flour Mo.)

69
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:21,590
(It was a disaster beyond imagining.)

70
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:25,150
(In Tangshan,
Eastern Hebei's industrial hub,)

71
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:28,240
(the earth shook; buildings fell.)

72
00:04:28,910 --> 00:04:29,750
(In an instant,)

73
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:32,400
(the entire city sank into darkness)

74
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,120
(and was flattened.)

75
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,680
(Water, power, and transport were down.)

76
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:41,710
(The Beijing-Tianjin-Tangshan
power grid was at risk.)

77
00:04:43,030 --> 00:04:45,240
(At that life-or-death moment,)

78
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:47,310
(our most beloved people,)

79
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,710
(the People's Liberation Army,)

80
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:53,870
(under the guidance
of Chairman Mao's revolutionary line...)

81
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,280
What are you thinking?

82
00:04:59,910 --> 00:05:01,750
The rain just won't stop.

83
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,590
It's normal.

84
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,910
Talk properly.

85
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,120
My good days are over.

86
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:12,150
So, can you handle me?

87
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:15,270
I can't.

88
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,000
Then what's your plan?

89
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:22,270
Tough it out.

90
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:29,310
What are you laughing at?

91
00:07:24,190 --> 00:07:25,870
You like this piece too?

92
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:29,110
Does it sound good?

93
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,680
This piece is called The Swan.

94
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,680
It's the most beautiful piece
in the world.

95
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:41,360
You don't have friends, do you?

96
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,480
It is my friend.

97
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,630
It sings me the most beautiful songs

98
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,510
and plays me the sweetest music.

99
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:00,560
You don't have friends either?

100
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,830
Will you be my friend, then?

101
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,120
What's a slut?

102
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:19,120
A torn shoe isn't called a slut.

103
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,720
Someone with a broken heart...

104
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,120
You'll understand when you grow up.

105
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,640
Come here.

106
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:42,390
Have you heard The Ugly Duckling?

107
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:50,630
There was a mother duck.

108
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:52,190
She had a bunch of ducklings.

109
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,480
Ducks don't give birth to ducklings.

110
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,830
They only lay eggs

111
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,600
and hatch the ducklings.

112
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:00,920
You're right.

113
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:04,190
So, a mother duck

114
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:06,630
hatched a bunch of ducklings.

115
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:11,390
But the last one to hatch

116
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,510
was different from all the others.

117
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:18,480
It hatched many days later.

118
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,720
It looked different
from the other ducks,

119
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:24,560
small and plain-looking.

120
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:27,390
The other ducks didn't like it

121
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,720
or play with it.

122
00:09:30,190 --> 00:09:32,190
It felt ugly itself.

123
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:36,480
So, it left the flock, heartbroken,

124
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:39,070
and hid in the grass.

125
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,560
Only at night,

126
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:44,240
when the other ducks were asleep,

127
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,870
could it come out to look for food.

128
00:09:48,430 --> 00:09:49,360
One day...

129
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:02,516
Do you want to hear more?

130
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:06,660
(Wardrobe and Makeup Room)

131
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,720
Winter passed, and spring came.

132
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:11,510
Flowers bloomed in the grass.

133
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,910
The Ugly Duckling grew up.

134
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,630
It found its courage

135
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:21,240
and swam into Swan Lake by day.

136
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,240
When it saw its reflection in the water,

137
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,390
it finally realized

138
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,670
that it was a white swan.

139
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:18,120
(Many soldiers' fingers)

140
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,240
(were worn to bloody pulps.)

141
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,080
Laidi.

142
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:22,750
What are you doing?

143
00:11:23,420 --> 00:11:24,270
It's raining.

144
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,390
Why run around outside?

145
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:26,920
Where are you going?

146
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,200
To pee.

147
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:30,240
How many times have I told you?

148
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,080
Girls should speak politely.

149
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:34,390
Say "Use the bathroom". Got it?

150
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,560
Got it?

151
00:11:37,450 --> 00:11:38,550
Where did you get the money?

152
00:11:38,550 --> 00:11:39,840
I just got paid today.

153
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:44,550
Two yuan.

154
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,280
Happy?

155
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:50,360
Your first-ever earnings.

156
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:51,840
Keep it safe.

157
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,440
Buy yourself something.

158
00:11:54,270 --> 00:11:55,110
Go on.

159
00:11:57,870 --> 00:11:59,960
(With firm resolve,)

160
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:02,790
(fearing nothing,
and overcoming all odds,)

161
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:05,360
(they fought their way to victory)

162
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:09,270
(and rushed
to the disaster-stricken zone.)

163
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:14,150
(Soldiers braved endless aftershocks,)

164
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,550
(dug through cracked slabs by hand,)

165
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:18,326
Director.

166
00:12:18,337 --> 00:12:19,870
(and shouldered the collapsed beams...)

167
00:12:19,870 --> 00:12:20,870
Why the panic?

168
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,960
You called it, Director.

169
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,750
That well really is acting strange.

170
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:29,030
When did it start bubbling?

171
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:31,600
I just came by and saw it bubbling.

172
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:37,360
Is the troupe asleep
in the earthquake shelter?

173
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,030
The troupe's all there, but Shoes Bai.

174
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,320
She locked herself in her room,

175
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,840
listening to that bourgeois music,

176
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,380
and refused to open up, no matter what.

177
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,750
Director, if I must,
I'll break down her door,

178
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,080
smash the gramophone,

179
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,550
and force her into the shelter.

180
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:50,600
Are you out of your mind?

181
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:51,840
That'd make us bullies.

182
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,270
Then what do we do?

183
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:59,270
Tell the troupe to sleep

184
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:00,630
with their clothes on tonight.

185
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,790
Got it. I'll notify them now.

186
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:04,120
Go, go. Tell them now.

187
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,150
Everyone, sleep in your clothes tonight.

188
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,630
There may be a quake tonight.

189
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:08,840
Everyone, stay alert.

190
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,720
You stay here. I'm heading back.

191
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:16,840
Director Huang.

192
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:21,360
Good timing. I need to talk to you.

193
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:24,150
What are you two doing here?

194
00:13:24,790 --> 00:13:26,750
Why wander around at a time like this?

195
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:28,270
Get back to the front shelter, now.

196
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:29,870
We need to talk to you.

197
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:32,440
I need a divorce certificate.

198
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:34,670
Zhang Guangrong agreed to the divorce.

199
00:13:35,270 --> 00:13:36,600
He wrote me a letter.

200
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,480
Do you want to see it?

201
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,270
You should just call him.

202
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:41,840
Divorce isn't just his call.

203
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,120
The Revolutionary Committee must decide.

204
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:46,360
Don't you run
the Revolutionary Committee?

205
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,823
Can we skip the discussion?

206
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:50,960
It's nothing to be proud of.

207
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:52,120
No.

208
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:38,390
Left, right, left.

209
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:41,480
1, 2, 3, 4.

210
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:44,480
(Ningzhou Department Store)
1, 2, 3, 4.

211
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,630
(Don't panic in an earthquake)
1, 2, 3, 4.

212
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:48,870
1, 2, 3, 4.

213
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,000
See the mountain across from us?

214
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:03,120
You need to send your voices

215
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,630
all the way to that mountain.

216
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:05,870
Fill the whole valley.

217
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:06,840
Got it?

218
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,270
That way, when we perform,

219
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:09,480
more people in the audience

220
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,960
can hear what you're singing.

221
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:14,626
♪Through the forest♪

222
00:15:14,670 --> 00:15:19,870
♪Through the forest♪

223
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:25,000
♪Across the snowy plains♪

224
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:31,000
♪Tragic and heroic♪

225
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:36,700
♪As it turned out♪

226
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:43,270
♪I was♪

227
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:50,630
♪Born in the wind
and raised in the rain♪

228
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:53,910
♪Grandma♪

229
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:01,550
What did you sing? Ms. Hua threw up!

230
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:04,080
Yeah. She kept howling next to me.

231
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:10,600
Little ball, banana, pear.

232
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,440
The Malan flower blooms at twenty-one.

233
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:16,150
Two-five-six, two-five-seven.

234
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:18,630
Two-eight, two-nine, thirty-one.

235
00:16:18,630 --> 00:16:19,960
You've got lice on you?

236
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:22,480
It feels good.

237
00:16:24,390 --> 00:16:27,080
Four-five-six, four-five-seven.

238
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:28,350
Come on.

239
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,870
Push, come on.

240
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,080
Push.

241
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,750
Push, push.

242
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:35,790
Push, come on.

243
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:37,110
Move, push.

244
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:39,080
Go on, push.

245
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:40,350
Come on.

246
00:16:40,790 --> 00:16:42,510
Push, push.

247
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:43,840
Go on, push.

248
00:16:44,790 --> 00:16:46,440
Push, push.

249
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:47,840
Stop it right now!

250
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:57,790
Trainee class, go!

251
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:58,670
Go!

252
00:16:58,670 --> 00:17:00,460
Hit him!

253
00:17:00,790 --> 00:17:01,720
Take him down!

254
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:05,470
Go!

255
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,390
Take him down!

256
00:17:06,390 --> 00:17:07,480
Hurry, hit him!

257
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:08,750
Hit him! Hit him!

258
00:17:10,390 --> 00:17:11,390
Right hook!

259
00:17:11,390 --> 00:17:12,550
Uppercut him!

260
00:17:13,270 --> 00:17:14,750
Hit the guy in the green cap!

261
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:16,600
Hit him, hit his face!

262
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,000
Sweep his legs!

263
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,510
Get him, get him!

264
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:23,630
Hit him!

265
00:17:23,630 --> 00:17:24,550
Hit him, hit him!

266
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:26,510
Trip him, grab his neck!

267
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:31,200
Come on, get up. Keep going.

268
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,910
Come on, get up.

269
00:17:35,790 --> 00:17:36,630
Run faster.

270
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,360
You fought, huh?

271
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:40,150
Two laps today.

272
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,080
Quit whining. Run faster.

273
00:17:43,550 --> 00:17:44,750
Whining will make it three.

274
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:56,600
Move.

275
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:57,600
Don't get in the way.

276
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,030
Move.

277
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:10,630
The injured.

278
00:18:10,670 --> 00:18:11,550
From Tangshan.

279
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:12,630
From Tangshan?

280
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,720
- Comrades.
- Make way, please.

281
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,030
The Tangshan earthquake

282
00:19:02,030 --> 00:19:03,000
Step aside, please.

283
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,270
has caused severe casualties.

284
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:07,310
The first group sent to our county

285
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:08,750
has already arrived.

286
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:11,070
The county hospital is short on blood.

287
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:14,510
The Revolutionary Committee

288
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:17,550
calls on all units to donate blood.

289
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:18,920
Comrades,

290
00:19:20,380 --> 00:19:23,680
the People's Liberation Army
is on the front line.

291
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:25,550
We can't fall behind.

292
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,350
We must give blood bravely too.

293
00:19:28,550 --> 00:19:29,590
Do you all agree?

294
00:19:29,590 --> 00:19:30,440
Agreed.

295
00:19:30,450 --> 00:19:31,300
- Yes.
- Yes!

296
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,400
Then get ready.

297
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:34,030
Meet at the troupe entrance.

298
00:19:34,030 --> 00:19:34,920
- Okay.
- Sure.

299
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,030
Come on, let's go.

300
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:37,400
Go, go, go!

301
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,350
Count me in. I'll donate blood too.

302
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:41,590
Not you. Your blood won't pass.

303
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:43,160
Why wouldn't my blood pass?

304
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:44,510
It's not pure.

305
00:19:45,510 --> 00:19:46,920
My blood isn't pure?

306
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,030
Not red enough.

307
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,070
Who are you trying to shame?

308
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:54,370
My blood isn't red?

309
00:19:54,370 --> 00:19:55,240
Have you even seen it?

310
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:56,110
No, I haven't.

311
00:20:01,350 --> 00:20:02,550
What's wrong with you?

312
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,400
Look. Is it red or not?

313
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:10,750
Stop messing around. Why jump in?

314
00:20:12,070 --> 00:20:13,440
Why can't I donate blood?

315
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:16,350
Your blood is full

316
00:20:17,110 --> 00:20:19,110
of arrogance, not discipline,

317
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:20,350
and you can't take a hint.

318
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:22,750
These are special times.

319
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,110
He finally found

320
00:20:24,110 --> 00:20:25,550
his own stage and got to be

321
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:26,720
the lead for once.

322
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:27,720
Yet you were so clueless.

323
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:28,750
Why steal his spotlight?

324
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:29,830
These are special times.

325
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:31,160
How can he treat it as a show?

326
00:20:31,698 --> 00:20:32,529
When you're drumming,

327
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:34,050
would you want someone twanging cotton

328
00:20:34,121 --> 00:20:34,785
right beside you?

329
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:37,550
You're totally on his side now.

330
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,960
You're turning into Zhu Zhengjing.

331
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:41,720
Pathetic.

332
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,350
I'll be back after the restroom break.

333
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:25,653
What are you staring at?

334
00:21:25,830 --> 00:21:27,750
Keep staring,
and I'll dig your eyes out.

335
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,960
Today, we saw

336
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:55,030
many injured people
being moved to our county,

337
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:58,110
and many were our age.

338
00:21:58,750 --> 00:21:59,720
When we saw them,

339
00:22:00,070 --> 00:22:02,750
we knew how severe, terrifying,

340
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:03,750
and cruel

341
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,070
the quake was.

342
00:22:06,350 --> 00:22:07,680
We were deeply shocked

343
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:09,350
and felt truly sorry for you.

344
00:22:09,790 --> 00:22:11,510
Chairman Mao taught us:

345
00:22:12,350 --> 00:22:15,920
Be firm, fear no sacrifice,

346
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:17,270
and overcome all odds to win.

347
00:22:17,830 --> 00:22:20,440
Let us remember his teachings

348
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:23,070
and be worthy successors to communism.

349
00:22:25,813 --> 00:22:26,706
This is the letter

350
00:22:26,717 --> 00:22:28,880
that Feng Xiaoxiao and I
wrote on behalf of our class.

351
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,270
What do you all think?

352
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:32,000
It sounds good.

353
00:22:32,590 --> 00:22:34,590
I think a letter is not enough.

354
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:36,270
We should do what our teacher did

355
00:22:36,270 --> 00:22:37,310
and make donations.

356
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:38,780
Raise your hand if you agree.

357
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,030
I'll donate 20 cents.

358
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:29,830
Yu Liping, 20 cents.

359
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,310
I'll give 20 cents too.

360
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,000
- What about you?
- 20 cents.

361
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,350
Liu Ke, 20 cents.

362
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:37,030
20 cents for me too.

363
00:23:38,110 --> 00:23:39,310
Zhang Heiwa, 20 cents.

364
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:40,270
I'll give 15 cents.

365
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,000
We don't make change here.

366
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,880
Then I'll give 10 cents.

367
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,070
Fine, fine.

368
00:23:46,350 --> 00:23:47,240
Take it.

369
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:48,400
Didn't you say no change?

370
00:23:49,030 --> 00:23:50,550
Have you no shame, bargaining

371
00:23:50,550 --> 00:23:51,640
with people in need?

372
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:52,640
Next. Next.

373
00:23:52,650 --> 00:23:53,510
Exactly.

374
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:54,350
I'll give 20 cents.

375
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:55,310
How much did Heiwa give?

376
00:23:55,310 --> 00:23:56,040
20 cents.

377
00:23:56,051 --> 00:23:57,240
Don't tell me it was 20 cents.

378
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,240
- Yeah, 20 cents.
- Chen Xiaoping, 10 cents.

379
00:24:02,070 --> 00:24:03,550
Chen Li, 10 cents.

380
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,750
Du Yufei, 10 cents.

381
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:09,493
Why aren't you chipping in?

382
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:12,400
Yi Qing'e.

383
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:14,830
Yi Qing'e, you're the only one left.

384
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,480
She's talking to you.

385
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:20,750
I don't have any money.

386
00:24:21,510 --> 00:24:22,400
Where's your money?

387
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,200
Yi Qing'e.

388
00:24:25,510 --> 00:24:26,920
Don't act like you can't hear me.

389
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:28,920
You raised your hand just now.

390
00:24:37,573 --> 00:24:38,653
You'll have to pay me back.

391
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:43,400
Yi Qing'e.

392
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:44,240
Watch.

393
00:24:49,270 --> 00:24:50,510
Let's see how much she gives.

394
00:24:50,510 --> 00:24:52,030
How much do you think she'll give?

395
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:56,550
How much did she give?

396
00:24:56,550 --> 00:24:57,790
How much?

397
00:24:57,790 --> 00:24:58,709
How much did she give?

398
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:01,240
How much?

399
00:25:02,350 --> 00:25:03,920
Yi Qing'e gave 5 cents.

400
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:04,760
5 cents?

401
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:06,440
So stingy.

402
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,440
Stingy.

403
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,280
Only 5 cents.

404
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:09,510
She has money but won't give.

405
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,000
- Yi Qing'e.
- Too stingy.

406
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,030
At least give 10 cents.

407
00:25:12,653 --> 00:25:13,830
How much can she possibly eat?

408
00:25:13,830 --> 00:25:15,160
She can't even spare 10 cents.

409
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:16,680
That's way too tightfisted.

410
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:17,680
What is she

411
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:20,240
saving it all for?

412
00:25:21,350 --> 00:25:23,270
How much food do you need?

413
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:25,030
Why is she like that?

414
00:25:25,030 --> 00:25:26,070
Exactly.

415
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,350
Where did you go?

416
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,160
What's going on here?

417
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,310
Why are you ignoring me?

418
00:25:55,110 --> 00:25:57,030
What's wrong? Who upset you?

419
00:25:57,790 --> 00:25:59,030
Tell me. I'll handle it for you.

420
00:26:00,110 --> 00:26:00,960
Is it Huang Zhengjing?

421
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:02,720
I don't want to talk to you.

422
00:26:03,550 --> 00:26:04,750
I didn't do anything, did I?

423
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,080
I'm expecting.

424
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:10,150
What?

425
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,280
I'm pregnant.

426
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:15,880
Go to Qin Feng.

427
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:18,200
Ask him to pull strings
at the Workers' Hospital.

428
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,720
The troupe can't find out.

429
00:26:20,830 --> 00:26:22,400
Shouldn't Zhang Guangrong know?

430
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,240
What do you mean?

431
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:25,750
He has a right to know.

432
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,640
Tell me what you really think.

433
00:26:29,510 --> 00:26:31,720
We can't decide a child's fate.

434
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:33,510
I'm not asking you to decide.

435
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:35,070
It's a life.

436
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,790
We can't decide that so casually.

437
00:26:39,510 --> 00:26:41,830
If he knows, the divorce is off.

438
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:46,750
You want to be a quitter?

439
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:49,030
I've never even been in a battle.

440
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:50,320
Get lost.

441
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:52,550
What's it to you?

442
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:10,700
(United against the quake)

443
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:29,560
Uncle.

444
00:27:30,030 --> 00:27:30,870
Uncle.

445
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:37,070
Why are you sitting here?

446
00:27:46,070 --> 00:27:48,160
You get ten days off soon.

447
00:27:48,510 --> 00:27:49,680
You can't go home.

448
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:52,640
Stay and drill your basic skills.

449
00:27:52,820 --> 00:27:54,320
You're slow, so you need a head start.

450
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,560
What's wrong?

451
00:28:00,146 --> 00:28:01,306
Did someone give you trouble?

452
00:28:03,750 --> 00:28:05,270
Or did you fall out with classmates?

453
00:28:15,640 --> 00:28:17,000
I'm not feeling great either.

454
00:28:18,110 --> 00:28:19,640
So, let's talk.

455
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:26,680
Did I embarrass you?

456
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:29,960
Did your classmates laugh at you?

457
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,310
Well, I had no choice

458
00:28:35,310 --> 00:28:36,750
about some things.

459
00:28:37,510 --> 00:28:39,790
You're young. You'll get it later.

460
00:28:42,110 --> 00:28:43,640
I was a handful as a kid.

461
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:47,720
If no one watched me,
I'd wreck the place.

462
00:28:48,110 --> 00:28:50,440
Your grandpa set me straight at home.

463
00:28:51,510 --> 00:28:52,720
After I grew up,

464
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,680
aside from drumming,

465
00:28:55,110 --> 00:28:57,000
I was hopeless at everything else.

466
00:28:58,350 --> 00:29:00,640
Life knocked me around out there, too.

467
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:06,240
When I first came from the village,

468
00:29:07,030 --> 00:29:08,400
I felt painfully small.

469
00:29:09,830 --> 00:29:11,750
But deep down, I made a vow.

470
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:14,030
I had to make these drums

471
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:17,000
sound better than anyone else's.

472
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,550
Others could look down on me,

473
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:22,110
but I couldn't look down on myself.

474
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,830
I lost my money.

475
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:29,200
What happened?

476
00:29:30,550 --> 00:29:32,200
I hid it in here. Now, it's gone.

477
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:35,880
You lost all of it?

478
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,310
Is this where you hide it?

479
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,400
You didn't see who took it?

480
00:29:51,550 --> 00:29:52,390
Forget it. It's fine.

481
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:54,390
I'll give you money.

482
00:29:54,790 --> 00:29:55,630
No need.

483
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:05,640
Come on. Come with me.

484
00:30:17,790 --> 00:30:18,630
Come on.

485
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:43,070
Come on, stop playing.

486
00:30:43,070 --> 00:30:45,030
Quick, listen to the PA!

487
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:48,160
Stop playing. Listen to the PA!

488
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,790
Everyone, listen to the PA!

489
00:30:49,790 --> 00:30:51,510
Zhou Yuzhi, listen to the PA!

490
00:30:51,510 --> 00:30:52,640
Who is it? Who?

491
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:53,550
Chu Jiahe.

492
00:30:53,550 --> 00:30:55,920
Listen to the PA. Go out and listen!

493
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:56,920
Who is it? Who?

494
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:57,830
It's Chu Jiahe.

495
00:30:57,830 --> 00:31:00,110
Everyone, listen. It's Chu Jiahe.

496
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:01,920
Let's go, Yi Qing'e.

497
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:03,110
Listen. It's Chu Jiahe.

498
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,350
Quiet, quiet.

499
00:31:05,350 --> 00:31:06,750
Listen to Chu Jiahe's broadcast.

500
00:31:09,270 --> 00:31:10,110
Sanyuan.

501
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:11,760
Where's Qiu?

502
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,960
He's probably by the gate,

503
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,200
playing Xiangqi with Gou.

504
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,400
He has time for Xiangqi? Seriously.

505
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:18,240
What's wrong?

506
00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:20,640
The whole troupe eats collectively now.

507
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,720
The grain ration for us isn't enough.

508
00:31:23,110 --> 00:31:24,213
I just collected

509
00:31:24,224 --> 00:31:25,640
everyone's grain ration booklets.

510
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:27,510
Go with Qiu

511
00:31:27,510 --> 00:31:28,350
and get the grain.

512
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:30,240
Fine. Leave it here, I'll go later.

513
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,550
Go now, hurry.

514
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:32,720
I still have to unload coal.

515
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:35,000
Xiuqin, come knead the dough.

516
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,110
Come on, come on.

517
00:31:36,110 --> 00:31:37,030
Hurry, hurry. Go now.

518
00:31:54,270 --> 00:31:55,750
Line up, line up.

519
00:31:55,750 --> 00:31:58,000
Plenty of grain,
supplied by a ration coupon.

520
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,830
Everyone, stand properly.

521
00:32:00,030 --> 00:32:01,480
Stay in line.

522
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,440
Everyone will get grain.

523
00:32:03,830 --> 00:32:05,750
Don't rush, and don't crowd.

524
00:32:05,750 --> 00:32:06,920
Line up.

525
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,033
Hurry, hurry. Line up.

526
00:32:08,044 --> 00:32:09,046
- Everyone.
- Take this.

527
00:32:09,057 --> 00:32:09,930
Line up, line up.

528
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,960
No rush. Everyone will get grain.

529
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:13,440
There's enough grain for everyone.

530
00:32:13,790 --> 00:32:14,920
Why are there so many people?

531
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,310
Is this buying grain or grabbing grain?

532
00:32:17,310 --> 00:32:18,790
They're storing grain now.

533
00:32:19,550 --> 00:32:20,400
One at a time.

534
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:22,310
You're young. Push in. I'll cover you.

535
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,200
My back's no good. I can't do it.

536
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:26,270
You're no use at all.

537
00:32:26,270 --> 00:32:27,380
Qiu, what good are you?

538
00:32:27,380 --> 00:32:28,270
Then you do it.

539
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:30,110
I'm in charge. I can't jump in.

540
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,350
How long will it take?

541
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:35,240
We all depend on this grain.

542
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:36,640
Come on, no rush. Take it easy.

543
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,480
Come on, come on.

544
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,400
Move faster up front.

545
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:40,950
I'll clear the crowd.

546
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:41,830
Grab the flour sack.

547
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:42,960
Get the first to buy grain.

548
00:32:43,550 --> 00:32:45,270
- How?
- I'm in a hurry.

549
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,310
- My turn!
- This way.

550
00:32:47,310 --> 00:32:48,350
Okay, come on.

551
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:52,240
Earthquake!

552
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:56,510
Earthquake! Earthquake!

553
00:32:56,510 --> 00:32:57,790
Hurry! Earthquake! Move!

554
00:32:57,790 --> 00:32:58,920
Slow down! Earthquake!

555
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:00,640
Slow down, slow down.

556
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,640
Easy, easy.

557
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,510
Grain sellers, stay put!

558
00:33:04,510 --> 00:33:05,350
It's okay. It's okay.

559
00:33:05,350 --> 00:33:06,830
- Hurry!
- Who's messing around?

560
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,920
- Come on!
- Who's spreading rumors?

561
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,000
Just nonsense. Who knows?

562
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,550
Come on, hurry. Grain ration booklet.

563
00:33:14,550 --> 00:33:15,390
Here.

564
00:33:17,970 --> 00:33:18,880
Here, here.

565
00:33:18,891 --> 00:33:19,962
Here. They're all in there.

566
00:33:19,973 --> 00:33:20,960
They're all in there.

567
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,510
Line up outside. Line up, everyone.

568
00:33:22,510 --> 00:33:23,480
No pushing. No pushing.

569
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:24,640
Stay in line. Stay in line.

570
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:25,480
Someone fell!

571
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,440
Someone fell from the building!

572
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:35,720
Someone fell!

573
00:33:37,350 --> 00:33:38,400
How could someone fall?

574
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:41,960
Who is that?

575
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,800
Who is it?

576
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,560
Is she okay?

577
00:33:45,110 --> 00:33:46,200
She can still move.

578
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:55,720
Move! Move!

579
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:57,720
Sanyuan, ride faster! Sanyuan!

580
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:03,790
Quiet. Almost there.

581
00:34:06,310 --> 00:34:08,200
- Hang in there.
- Slow down.

582
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:09,440
- Make way.
- Slow down.

583
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:10,790
Quiet. Almost there.

584
00:34:10,790 --> 00:34:12,070
It still hurts? Quiet.

585
00:34:12,070 --> 00:34:14,620
(Ningzhou People's Hospital)

586
00:34:14,640 --> 00:34:15,880
Careful. Let us through.

587
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:23,030
From Beijing

588
00:34:24,790 --> 00:34:26,003
to Hebei. We're in Shaanxi.

589
00:34:26,014 --> 00:34:26,960
Director, you needed me?

590
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:29,070
Shanxi saw changes too, right?

591
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:30,720
Yeah.

592
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:35,720
Hua Caixiang,

593
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:38,106
where are you going?
Let's have a meeting.

594
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,440
Have a seat.

595
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,240
Comrade Hua Caixiang,

596
00:34:56,830 --> 00:34:58,200
I asked you to come today...

597
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:01,480
Have you seen enough?

598
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,000
There's a meeting in here.

599
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:04,960
Go on, move along.

600
00:35:07,510 --> 00:35:08,680
Comrade Hua Caixiang,

601
00:35:09,350 --> 00:35:11,350
this meeting

602
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:13,680
is about your divorce application.

603
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:16,790
The Revolutionary Committee has decided

604
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,680
that your divorce application

605
00:35:19,270 --> 00:35:20,680
won't be approved for now.

606
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:21,520
Why?

607
00:35:21,790 --> 00:35:22,630
Why?

608
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:25,720
Divorce is a major life decision.

609
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:29,350
I hope you'll cool off first.

610
00:35:30,510 --> 00:35:31,920
Don't act on impulse.

611
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:34,720
You're right.

612
00:35:35,270 --> 00:35:36,310
I do act

613
00:35:36,310 --> 00:35:37,550
on impulse.

614
00:35:37,550 --> 00:35:38,920
You leaders know me best.

615
00:35:40,550 --> 00:35:42,480
Then, when will it be approved?

616
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:47,440
When...?

617
00:35:48,110 --> 00:35:49,230
Comrade Hua Caixiang,

618
00:35:49,670 --> 00:35:52,510
marriage is a private matter,

619
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:54,630
but you're different.

620
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:57,070
You're our star performer

621
00:35:57,070 --> 00:35:58,630
and a county celebrity.

622
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,030
Think of the last photo incident.

623
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:03,070
It hurt you personally

624
00:36:03,070 --> 00:36:05,190
and the troupe.

625
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:06,880
So, the organization

626
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:08,630
hopes that through this,

627
00:36:08,630 --> 00:36:10,440
you can raise your political awareness.

628
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:12,920
Now that you put it that way, I get it.

629
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:16,320
I didn't just marry Zhang Guangrong.

630
00:36:16,710 --> 00:36:18,190
I married the whole troupe.

631
00:36:18,670 --> 00:36:20,030
The troupe trained me.

632
00:36:20,030 --> 00:36:21,400
It gave me a stage.

633
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:23,800
It brought me so many honors.

634
00:36:24,110 --> 00:36:26,230
I should protect the troupe's honor.

635
00:36:26,710 --> 00:36:29,190
I should always put the troupe first.

636
00:36:29,630 --> 00:36:31,550
I can't let my private matters

637
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,110
affect the troupe.

638
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,440
Have a look.
Is this political awareness?

639
00:36:46,340 --> 00:36:48,820
(Abortion Application)

640
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,670
Abortion application?

641
00:37:06,746 --> 00:37:08,456
When Zhang Guangrong
came home last time,

642
00:37:08,467 --> 00:37:10,122
(Abortion Application)
we got careless,

643
00:37:10,133 --> 00:37:10,960
and I got pregnant.

644
00:37:11,630 --> 00:37:13,360
If I have this baby,

645
00:37:13,670 --> 00:37:16,400
it's ten months.
Then, postpartum confinement.

646
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:19,190
Nursing takes at least half a year.

647
00:37:19,190 --> 00:37:20,360
With all that,

648
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:22,320
I couldn't perform for two years.

649
00:37:23,550 --> 00:37:25,030
Thanks to your guidance,

650
00:37:25,030 --> 00:37:27,440
I realized I can't let personal matters

651
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,110
affect the troupe's shows.

652
00:37:29,110 --> 00:37:30,230
So, I can't keep

653
00:37:30,230 --> 00:37:31,070
this baby.

654
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:40,030
Hello, this is Huang Zhengjing.

655
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:43,280
What?

656
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:47,030
Okay, okay. Got it.

657
00:37:47,630 --> 00:37:48,800
I'll send someone over now.

658
00:37:52,150 --> 00:37:53,000
Hu Sanyuan

659
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,190
got picked up again.

660
00:37:54,630 --> 00:37:55,760
What happened this time?

661
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:02,320
Watch it next time.

662
00:38:03,190 --> 00:38:04,030
Go.

663
00:38:08,250 --> 00:38:09,150
Comrade,

664
00:38:09,190 --> 00:38:11,110
we're with Ningzhou County Troupe.

665
00:38:11,510 --> 00:38:13,510
Is Hu Sanyuan being held here?

666
00:38:14,070 --> 00:38:15,880
We're here to bring quilts.

667
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:17,840
Blankets, huh?

668
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,320
Sign in first.

669
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:21,110
- Right.
- Here, sign in.

670
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:21,960
Give me the quilts.

671
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:23,230
The top one is Hu Sanyuan's.

672
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:26,400
Comrade, well.

673
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:29,070
They only slipped up on the job.

674
00:38:29,550 --> 00:38:31,510
They're usually very motivated.

675
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:33,770
Both of them are poor
and lower-middle peasants.

676
00:38:33,780 --> 00:38:34,670
Both of them, right?

677
00:38:34,670 --> 00:38:35,710
Of course.

678
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,480
Could you handle this

679
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:39,760
as contradictions among the people?

680
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,480
That's not for us to decide.

681
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:43,680
Take it

682
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:46,030
to Earthquake Relief Headquarters.

683
00:38:47,510 --> 00:38:48,760
Okay, okay.

684
00:38:49,110 --> 00:38:51,190
Can we at least meet them?

685
00:38:51,190 --> 00:38:52,280
- Right.
- Meet them?

686
00:38:52,320 --> 00:38:53,160
They're over there.

687
00:38:54,760 --> 00:38:55,710
What's wrong with you?

688
00:38:56,800 --> 00:38:57,800
What a pair of idiots.

689
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:58,760
Why did you yell that?

690
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,760
He yelled first, so I yelled too.

691
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:02,230
Do you have to be as dumb as he is?

692
00:39:02,230 --> 00:39:04,760
Half your life is wasted.
Serves you right.

693
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:05,600
Serves you right.

694
00:39:06,230 --> 00:39:07,070
Dachui,

695
00:39:07,190 --> 00:39:08,190
pull some strings.

696
00:39:08,710 --> 00:39:09,960
What strings do I have?

697
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:13,186
Does Hua Caixiang know about this?

698
00:39:13,330 --> 00:39:14,190
Of course.

699
00:39:14,190 --> 00:39:16,320
If she hadn't,
why would I bring you a quilt?

700
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:18,360
She also asked me to tell you this:

701
00:39:19,230 --> 00:39:20,920
Do a good job firing bricks in there.

702
00:39:27,030 --> 00:39:28,036
What are you looking at?

703
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:29,550
Looking for your uncle?

704
00:39:31,110 --> 00:39:32,630
Your uncle's nothing but trouble.

705
00:39:33,030 --> 00:39:34,230
What kind of person is he?

706
00:39:34,550 --> 00:39:36,670
He went for grain and got arrested.

707
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,630
And he dragged Qiu down with him.

708
00:39:39,333 --> 00:39:40,670
I don't know what I was thinking.

709
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:42,110
Sending those two to buy grain.

710
00:39:42,110 --> 00:39:43,670
One Hu, one Qiu.

711
00:39:43,670 --> 00:39:46,000
With them together, chaos is guaranteed.

712
00:40:03,030 --> 00:40:03,920
Where's my uncle?

713
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:09,190
Adding bricks to the grand cause.

714
00:40:10,710 --> 00:40:12,320
The police got him again?

715
00:40:15,360 --> 00:40:17,630
How did you get
such a fool for an uncle?

716
00:40:18,630 --> 00:40:19,960
He went out just to buy grain

717
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,480
and ended up in a labor-camp kiln.

718
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,190
What can I say?

719
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:26,320
When is he coming back?

720
00:40:26,670 --> 00:40:28,960
No idea. I hope he fires bricks forever.

721
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,510
Then everyone in the county

722
00:40:30,510 --> 00:40:32,110
can live in brick houses.

723
00:40:38,230 --> 00:40:39,280
Liu Ke, you loser.

724
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:40,230
I'm not waiting for you.

725
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:42,170
Hurry up.

726
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:43,030
Come to my place.

727
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:43,940
Vacation at last.

728
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:46,480
Heiwa, aren't you going home?

729
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:47,320
No.

730
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:48,630
Then keep an eye on the place.

731
00:40:48,630 --> 00:40:49,470
Got it.

732
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:54,710
Just the two of us again.

733
00:40:58,480 --> 00:40:59,320
What's wrong?

734
00:41:02,630 --> 00:41:03,840
I need a favor.

735
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:05,320
What is it?

736
00:41:08,190 --> 00:41:09,960
Put in a word with Director Huang.

737
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,230
Ask him to tell the police

738
00:41:12,230 --> 00:41:13,550
to let my uncle out.

739
00:41:14,070 --> 00:41:15,480
The police got him again?

740
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:17,920
What was it this time?

741
00:41:21,150 --> 00:41:22,630
I don't dare to tell Director Huang.

742
00:41:23,710 --> 00:41:25,030
He's your uncle.

743
00:41:25,630 --> 00:41:27,480
He won't let me call him that.

744
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:29,190
He doesn't like me at all.

745
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:31,440
He never even looks at me.

746
00:41:32,070 --> 00:41:34,360
I have to avoid him whenever I see him.

747
00:41:40,110 --> 00:41:42,920
Little brats, just you two?

748
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:45,640
What are you doing?

749
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:51,960
Shame on you.

750
00:41:58,400 --> 00:41:59,240
Fine.

751
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:02,670
You think you're tough now, huh?

752
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:04,200
Just wait.

753
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:13,230
Two blockheads.

754
00:42:18,060 --> 00:42:23,300
(Always stay alert for quakes)

755
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:28,550
The bubbles are really surging today.

756
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:30,630
The water level
keeps rising and falling.

757
00:42:30,630 --> 00:42:31,670
That's not normal.

758
00:42:32,590 --> 00:42:34,550
The County Earthquake
Prevention Command Center

759
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:37,760
reports odd signs countywide
for two days.

760
00:42:38,190 --> 00:42:39,230
Very suspicious.

761
00:42:39,710 --> 00:42:41,510
They want all units on high alert.

762
00:42:42,070 --> 00:42:44,070
High alert, high alert.

763
00:42:44,070 --> 00:42:46,000
We've been on high alert
for over a month.

764
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,230
Will it really happen?

765
00:42:48,710 --> 00:42:50,230
Do you want it

766
00:42:50,230 --> 00:42:51,630
to happen?

767
00:42:51,630 --> 00:42:52,470
Well, Director.

768
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:55,000
If it never happens,
we can't prove ourselves.

769
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:56,190
But if it really happens,

770
00:42:56,190 --> 00:42:57,190
it might get out of hand.

771
00:42:57,190 --> 00:42:58,030
Stay on alert.

772
00:42:58,710 --> 00:42:59,550
Okay.

773
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:01,720
Sure, okay.

774
00:43:02,030 --> 00:43:03,110
Stay on alert.

775
00:43:03,110 --> 00:43:03,960
Okay, got it.

776
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

777
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:10,360
Comrade Zhang Guangrong

778
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:11,270
is taking back

779
00:43:11,270 --> 00:43:12,840
his agreement to divorce you.

780
00:43:13,150 --> 00:43:14,030
Where are you going?

781
00:43:14,190 --> 00:43:16,360
To the provincial capital,
for something big.

782
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:18,070
Laidi, come and help me.

783
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:20,440
A bone fracture in the shin.

784
00:43:20,440 --> 00:43:22,000
The surrounding soft tissue is damaged.

785
00:43:22,096 --> 00:43:23,222
What about practice routines?

786
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:24,620
That depends on how she heals.

787
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:25,960
What are you doing?

788
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:27,030
- Go away.
- Shoes Bai.

789
00:43:27,030 --> 00:43:28,360
- Shoes Bai.
- Shoes Bai.

790
00:43:30,100 --> 00:43:30,980
Uncle.

791
00:43:30,980 --> 00:43:32,260
Something's wrong with Shoes Bai.

792
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:33,760
Go take a look.

793
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

794
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

795
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

796
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

797
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

798
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

799
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

800
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

801
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

802
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

803
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

804
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

805
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

806
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

807
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

808
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

809
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

810
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

811
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

812
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

813
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪
